<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 11 mm. The triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum places this species in a group together with 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aureus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aureus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. aureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. trilinea" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="trilinea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. trilinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. trivittatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="trivittatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. trivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. From the latter two species, 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aureoscutus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aureoscutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. aureoscutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by the absence of golden pile along the anterior and lateral margins of the mesoscutum. The species differs from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. aureus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="aureus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. aureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the triangle of golden pile on the mesoscutum being wider than long and restricted to the posterior half of the mesoscutum. In the male, the ratio vertex width:head width is approximately 1:4.3 (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–24" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 19 - 24. 19, 20 Head dorsal: 19 Peradon aureoscutus male holotype (HW = head width, VW = vertex width) 20 P. aureus male Ecuador CNC 21 - 24 Tergite 2 dorsal: 21 Peradon aureoscutus male holotype 22 P. aureus male Ecuador CNC 23 P. trilinea male holotype 24 P. trivittatus male French Guiana RMNH." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures19-24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362276" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures19-24">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), and the lateral margins of tergite 2 are rather evenly diverging posteriad. Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 256–261" captionStartId="F44" captionText="Figures 256 - 261. Male genitalia of Peradon species 256 P. fenestratus French Guyana MNHN 257 P. aureoscutus holotype 258 P. aureus Ecuador CNC 259 P. trilinea holotype 260 P. trivittatus Suriname RMNH 261 P. hermetia holotype." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362314" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures256-261">Fig. 257</figureCitation>
. The female is unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
